content: I guess this is where some perspective might be helpful, but will leave to you to determine. I haven't been able to get interviews for leadership roles at all. I've also been unsuccessful in getting individual contributor roles at very low salaries, so I'm not sure. My actual goal is not a leadership role, it is just to get a good paying job, but if saying my goal is a leadership role is the best way for me to get an individual contributor role that is good paying, or at least better than uber and get my foot in the door at a company where I can work my way up, then that's fine. It seems that employers are very sensitive to bringing someone on that is overqualified, so I'm not really sure how to approach
